<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718>
    dc:creator "Naruse, Tohru", "Schubart, Christoph D.", "Shih, Hsi-Te" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Molecular evidence and differences in gonopod morphology lead to the recognition of a new species of the freshwater crab genus Candidiopotamon Bott, 1967 (Crustacea, Brachyura, Potamidae) from eastern Taiwan" ;
    bibo:endPage "196" ;
    bibo:journal "ZooKeys" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-09-11" ;
    bibo:startPage "169" ;
    bibo:volume "1179" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure5> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Collection sites for Candidiopotamon rathbuni (De Man, 1914) (circles) and Candidiopotamon penglai sp. nov. (squares) in Taiwan, as well as other congeners from the Ryukyus, Japan. Different colors indicate sampling sites of clades. Dotted lines indicate the possible biogeographic boundaries between clades NW, W, SW, S, SE, E 1, and E 2, corresponding to the color in Fig. 2; as well as species. The red star and blue star indicate the type localities of C. rathbuni and C. penglai sp. nov., respectively. Three forms of male left G 1 are shown for clades in C. rathbuni and two forms for clades in C. penglai sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/904107" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Candidiopotamon rathbuni (De Man, 1914): male (44.6 x 36.8 mm) from Chiayi, western Taiwan (RUMF-ZC- 86) (A - E); male (35.4 x 31.2 mm) from Miaoli, northwestern Taiwan (NCHUZOOL 15194) (F 1); male (36.7 x 31.1 mm) from Chiayi, western Taiwan (NCHUZOOL 15205) (F 2); male (36.3 x 30.7 mm) from Taiwu, Pingtung, southwestern Taiwan (NCHUZOOL 15199) (F 3). A carapace, dorsal view B carapace, frontal view C male major chela, outer view D 1 left G 1, ventral view D 2 left G 1, dorsal view D 3 left G 1 terminal segment, dorsal view E left G 2 F 1 - 3 left G 1 s terminal segment, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A - C); 2 mm (D - F). Arrow indicates the keel-like projection on the distal inner edge of the terminal segment." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/904109" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Color in life of Candidiopotamon rathbuni (De Man, 1914) (A, B) and Candidiopotamon penglai sp. nov. (C-F). A, C, E overall dorsal view B, D, F overall ventral view A, B NCHUZOOL 15181 (male, 28.0 x 23.9 mm, Rihyuetan, Nantou, western Taiwan) C, D NCHUZOOL 15204 (male, 39.7 x 34.4 mm, Nanrenshan, Pingtung, southern Taiwan); NCHUZOOL 15224 (paratype male, 36.4 x 30.9 mm, Liyu Lake, Shoufeng, Hualien, eastern Taiwan)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/904110" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1179.106718.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Color in life of Candidiopotamon rathbuni (De Man, 1914) (A-D) and Candidiopotamon penglai sp. nov. (E-H). A, B NCHUZOOL 15194 (male, 35.4 x 31. 2 mm, Tai-an, Miaoli, northwestern Taiwan) C NCHUZOOL 15211 (male, 24.8 x 22.1 mm, Dongshih, Taichung, western Taiwan) D NCHUZOOL 15181 (male, 28.0 x 23.9 mm, Rihyuetan, Nantou, western Taiwan) E, F NCHUZOOL 15204 (2 males, 39.7 x 34.4 mm, 40.6 x 34.3 mm, Nanrenshan, Pingtung, southern Taiwan) G NCHUZOOL 15224 (paratype male, 36.4 x 30.9 mm, Liyu Lake, Shoufeng, Hualien, eastern Taiwan) H NCHUZOOL 15229 (male, 33.1 x 29.7 mm, Jili Lake, Guangfu, Hualien, eastern Taiwan)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/904111" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

